<div id="review_2391411837" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2391411837" />
    <a title="Mila" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57432835-mila"><img alt="Mila" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1557417719p2/57432835.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2391411837?book_show_action=true">Dec 26, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mila" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mila" href="/user/show/57432835-mila">Mila</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/28958666-hour-of-the-bees">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2391411837" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3023042083351141805">I may have enjoyed this book a bit more than some other did because one of its topics hit really close to my heart. My grandma&apos;s last 2 years of life were marked by quite severe dementia and as I spent some time looking after her, this time will stay forever in my memory. So I was glad to see a sort of similar experience represented in a middle-grade novel and I liked the story and the characters quite a lot.</span>
  <span id="freeText3023042083351141805" style="display:none">I may have enjoyed this book a bit more than some other did because one of its topics hit really close to my heart. My grandma's last 2 years of life were marked by quite severe dementia and as I spent some time looking after her, this time will stay forever in my memory. So I was glad to see a sort of similar experience represented in a middle-grade novel and I liked the story and the characters quite a lot.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3023042083351141805" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


